# Why: SaaS-billing Phase 1 — surface trial / internal-org state on the
#      in-app billing page. New external orgs get a 14-day Pro trial on
#      signup (overlay 041); without UI feedback they have no way to know
#      they're on a trial or when it ends. This patch adds a small banner
#      at the top of `/o/<orgUrl>/settings/billing` that reads from the
#      new `bizrethink.organisationBilling.get` TRPC procedure
#      (additive in packages/bizrethink/server-only/trpc/) and renders
#      one of three states:
#        - bizrethinkInternal=true     → blue "BizRethink Internal" badge
#        - trialEndsAt > now (>3 days) → indigo "Pro trial active, N days"
#        - trialEndsAt > now (<=3 days)→ amber "Pro trial active, N days" urgent
#        - trialEndsAt <= now          → red "Trial ended" with upgrade CTA
#        - no row / loading            → renders nothing (silent fallback)
# Why-not-additive: The billing route file is upstream Documenso
#      (`apps/remix/app/routes/_authenticated+/o.$orgUrl.settings.billing.tsx`).
#      A new React component can live in `packages/bizrethink/ui/` long-term,
#      but doing that for a single small component now means adding
#      `@documenso/trpc`, `@documenso/ui`, and React deps to the bizrethink
#      package — overkill for one banner. The component is defined inline
#      in the patch (PactaBillingBanner, ~50 lines) and rendered above the
#      existing billing UI. When we add more BizRethink in-app components
#      later, extract this into `packages/bizrethink/ui/billing/`.
# Upstream-merge-fragility: LOW. The patch adds new lines at the top of
#      the file (component definition) and one JSX node insertion at the
#      start of the return value. Upstream Documenso would have to delete
#      the entire billing page or rename it for this to break. Watch for
#      restructuring of the billing route during weekly sync.
# Pairs with: bizrethink.organisationBilling.get TRPC procedure at
#      packages/bizrethink/server-only/trpc/organisation-billing-router.ts
#      (additive, wired into top-level bizrethinkRouter at router.ts).
